Here are highlights of Lucille Ball's career:

1926 _ Begins career in show business in New York as a chorus girl.
1940 _ Marries Desi Arnaz, a Cuban percussionist and bandleader when both were making the movie "Too Many Girls."
1962 _ Miss Ball goes solo, returning to the airwaves in "The Lucy Show."
1968 _ "The Lucy Show" is redesigned and becomes "Here's Lucy."
1974 _ Miss Ball plays the title role in the movie version of "Mame."
1986 _ Miss Ball returns to sitcom television in ABC's "Life With Lucy."
The show is canceled within months.
